ath"],"importance":5}],"summary":"This batch primarily consisted of Amharic words prefixed with 'የ' (the genitive/possessive marker) and often suffixed with 'ም' (also/and), 'ን' (object marker), 'ውን' (definite article + object marker), or 'ቸውን' (possessive suffix + object marker). \n\nPROTOCOL 1 (THE SPLITTER) and 3 (THE CORRECTOR) were applied to remove these prefixes and suffixes, yielding the clean base word for the 'word' field. For example, 'የዓለሙንም' was split and cleaned to 'ዓለም'.\n\nPROTOCOL 4 (THE LEMMATIZER) was crucial for identifying the base dictionary form. For many entries, especially proper nouns, the cleaned word itself served as the root (e.g., 'ዐይናለም' -> 'ዐይናለም'). For plural nouns or words with additional morphological changes, the singular or base form was identified (e.g., 'ዓመታት' -> 'ዓመት', 'ዑዝኤላውያን' -> 'ዑዝኤል', 'ዓመፀኞች' -> 'ዓመፀኛ', 'ዓረባውያን' -> 'ዓረባዊ').\n\nScholarly Guesses were made for 'ዒዋም', 'ዓልም', and 'ዓብዳም', treating them as single proper nouns rather than attempting further morphological decomposition, as their structure strongly suggests proper names in the context of other biblical names in the batch. 'ዐግንም' was split into 'ዐግን' (proper noun) and the suffix 'ም'.\n\nPROTOCOL 2 (THE JUDGE) found no gibberish or unfixable errors. PROTOCOL 7 (THE FILTER) confirmed all cleaned words and roots were at least two characters long. PROTOCOL 5 (THE TRANSLATOR) and 6 (THE GRAMMARIAN) were applied to provide comprehensive English synonyms and Part of Speech tags, respectively.","input_words":["የዐይናለም","የዐዲስ","የዐድሜ","የዐግንም","የዑሪ","የዑስና","የዑዝኤላውያንም","የዑዝኤልን","የዒር","የዒርናሐሽንም","የዒዋም","የዒዶ","የዓለሙንም","የዓልም","የዓመታትም","የዓመታትን","የዓመታዊውን","የዓመፀኞችን","የዓመፀኞችንም","የዓመፃቸውን","የዓመፅንም","የዓሚኤል","የዓምዱም","የዓሢኤል","የዓሣም","የዓሣን","የዓረባውያንን","የዓብዳም","የዓብድኤልንም","የዓናት"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"4b4bb0f0-9e79-4269-b14f-2735f2c58e76","created_at":"2026-03-02T14:58:47.436131+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_25/chunk_040